comments.text:
I have serious globophobia which is a fear of balloons. For me, it's really 
only rubber balloons that bother me because of the sudden and loud sound 
they make when popped. When I see a baby or a mentally challenged person 
just playing with a balloon, I start to feel really uncomfortable because 
I'm afraid it's going to pop in their mouth or face. It's just the 
anticipation of it being popped that freaks me out. I have to walk away 
from the room and go somewhere else so I don't feel nervous. Anyway, as 
benign as balloons are, I'd have to punch Ellen in the face if she was 
shoving balloons in my face. I love Ellen and I'd feel really bad after 
that, but it's just a natural reaction for me when people start trying to 
make a balloon pop because they know it scares me. Love you, Ellen!!!﻿
